    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on Monte Carlo UQ results demonstrating 95th-percentile hemolysis index below the absolute clinical threshold across all five operating points, and on velocity field agreement (RMS error 7.8%) against the FDA PIV benchmark. Six credibility factors remain at not-assessed status; these are acknowledged as epistemic gaps. Re-validation of the model against a refreshed experimental dataset following the January 2026 revision is planned for Q2 2026. The team judged the existing 2025-Q4 PIV data sufficient as an interim anchor pending that re-validation.",
